## Advanced Stance Tactics

### Stance Dancing

Skilled combatants don't marry their initial stance—they flow between stances as combat develops:

**Opening: Defensive** - Start safely, build Momentum while enemies close distance or reveal their tactics. Generate +1-2 Momentum from being attacked and defending successfully.

**Mid-Combat: Aggressive** - Switch to Aggressive (costs Momentum) after building resources. Spend accumulated Momentum on powerful techniques while dealing increased damage.

**Endgame: Balanced** - Switch to Balanced as combat winds down. Clean up remaining enemies while maintaining defensive options.

This pattern—defend, attack, adapt—creates a combat rhythm that maximizes Momentum economy while minimizing risk.

### Role Swapping

Your stance can change with your role:

**Fighter Example:**
- Starts Aggressive (deal damage, pressure enemies)
- Takes heavy damage from focused enemy attention
- Switches to Defensive (survive, recover)
- Healer restores Fighter
- Switches back to Aggressive (finish weakened enemies)

The ability to change roles mid-combat through stance switching creates dynamic fights that don't lock characters into single approaches.

### Coordinated Stance Changes

Advanced parties coordinate stance switches for tactical advantage:

**Turn Order Manipulation:**
- Rogue starts Aggressive (acts first, eliminates high-value target)
- Switches to Balanced next turn (acts second, responds to enemy tactics)
- This deliberate turn order change creates tactical flexibility

**Momentum Generation Optimization:**
- Wizard starts Defensive (builds Momentum safely)
- Fighter starts Aggressive (generates Momentum through attacks)
- Both parties build resources simultaneously through different methods
- Mid-combat, both have Momentum to spend on powerful options

